description:
In this episode, we learn about the Great Disappointment. In the early 1840's, people all over the world were expecting Jesus to return after reformers and preachers like William Miller studied of the prophecies of Daniel. However, after the expected time came and left in 1844, they were bitterly disappointed. How did they cope with this and how did God lead them through?

To find out more about the Great Disappointment please read our extended article on our website. 
https://lineagejourney.com/read/the-great-disappointment/
